track.name: She Moves Me
comments: Little Walter on the harp. I love Muddy Waters & he sure always had a great blues band.
thru the rok,cntry,jazz,whatever...aint nuthin like coming bak to hear the DOG!!!
This was part of our set back in the 60's - magic man

this song is the birth of amplified harp on record.  they'd been playing that style for ages but the producer (who's doing drumming here - hence it being a bit all over the place) finally allowed walter's new sound loose on a recording on this very track.  what a beautiful piece of musical history.

this guy was a genius. amazing. don't mean to advertise, that ain't my style... but you guys might like my stuff maybe. i was around in muddy's time, but i still make music these days. http://www.last.fm/music/B.C.+Williamson but back to muddy for now!
